SIMPLE: unturned
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unturned
<hw>Un*turned"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>turned</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not turned; not revolved
or reversed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To leave no stone unturned</b></col>, <cd>to leave
nothing untried for accomplishing one's purpose.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] <qex>left unturned no stone</qex>⟦br⟧
To make my guilt appear, and hide his own.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untwain</ent>⟦br⟧
